quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  16,35,"And those who had associated<i class=""s"">(others with Allah) </i>said, “Had Allah willed, we would never have worshiped anything apart from Him—neither us, nor our forefathers, nor would we have prohibited anything without<i class=""s"">(permission from) </i>Him.” Those before them did likewise. So are the messengers responsible for anything but evident proclamation?"
  16,36,"For very truly, in every community We sent a messenger: “Worship<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Allah and avoid false masters.” So some of them Allah has guided, and some of them have deserved misguidance. So journey{1}through the earth and look what the outcome was for the disbelievers.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 2nd person.
  16,37,"<i class=""s"">(Even) </i>if you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are concerned about their guidance,<i class=""s"">(still) </i><span class=""h"">Allah surely does not guide whomever He leads<sup foot_note=""80385"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">astray</span>, and they will have no helpers."
  16,38,"And they have sworn by Allah their most solemn oaths that Allah does not resurrect whoever dies. Yes indeed, it is a promise binding on Him, but the majority of mankind does not know."
  16,39,"<i class=""s"">(This is) </i>to clarify for them what they differ over, and so that those who have denied know that they were liars."
  16,40,"Indeed, Our only saying to anything, once We have wanted it, is to say to it, <span class=""h"">“Be,” and so it is<sup foot_note=""80386"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>."
  16,41,"And those who emigrated for Allah after they had been dealt with unjustly—We will surely settle them in a good place in the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>, and the reward of the Hereafter is truly greater, if they only knew."
  16,42,"Those are the ones who endured patiently, and in their Lord they place{1}their trust.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.
